Add missing rows

add_missing_years.Rd

claims_data is requested to only contain rows in which one of Cl_reserve, An_reserve, Cl_payment_cal or An_payment_cal is not equal to 0.
This step adds rows so that claims_data contains one row per calendar year between the origin year and the last origin year for each claim.

This function resembles only step 2 of the data preparation process, see description in details of prepare_data()

Usage

add_missing_years(claims_data, last_orig_year)

Arguments

claims_data

dataframe after step 1, see details of prepare_data().

last_orig_year

Integer value for the last origin year which will also be treated as the last calendar year, usually the calendar year just ended, see details of prepare_data().

Value

dataframe with added rows
